If you're looking for a pretty pistol, hit the back button now. If you're one of those people that thinks "a Glock is a Glock and all Glocks are worth $450" then, please, hit the back button now. It comes off easily and I can remove it before you buy it. NO, I'm not going to give this gun away for cheap just because it has a light coat of spray paint on the frame and light.
This is a Glock 17 RTF 2 with "fish gill" serrations. I'm not going to go too far into the details of the RTF II because if you're read this far then you already know all that stuff. This one has a Lone Wolf threaded barrel, Trijicon Heinie night sights, factory extended mag release, factory extended slide release and it also comes with a metal low profile mag well funnel. I forgot the manufacture's name for this magwell but it was like $120 and was designed to be smaller and less absurd-looking than the huge competition ones but still aid in mag changes duty use. 
 
This is a gunfighter's gun. It doesn't want to be stuck in a safe or shot at some bull-crap indoor range while standing still and punching holes in paper zombie targets with an RSO standing over your shoulder. This gun BEGS to be run hard by a hard bastard. It holds a TIGHT group with that match barrel from Lone Wolf. Mag changes are a snap with the magwell funnel. The light is a Streamlight M3 and the extender on the mag is factory Glock +2 extender. I have a TON of Glock 17 mags. This ad essentially includes ONE mag but I can add more depending on your trade. 
 
Oh, and I have the box and all the stuff that came in the box... but, again, consider trade offers starting with one mag coming with this gun and we can negotiate up as-needed. I know a lot of Glock people already have a bunch of 17 mags.
